distinctive /dɪˈstɪŋktɪv/

1. ADJ Something that is distinctive has a special quality or feature which makes it easily recognizable and different from other things of the same type. 与众不同的; 有特色的 

例： ...the distinctive odour of chlorine. …氯气的特殊气味。 

2. distinctively ADV 特别地; 有特色地 [ADV adj/-ed] 

例： ...the distinctively fragrant taste of elderflowers. …接骨木花奇特的香味。

